                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 839.00/1781</note>
                <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Santo Domingo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-01-19T17:00:00-04:40">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 19, 1916, 5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>I think the Department should be prepared for probable difficulty in this country
                    soon. Congress adjourned for the holidays and although due to meet on the 11th
                    has not convened as yet.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Russell</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
